        data-piece="rook" data-type="movements"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full lg:w-7/12 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="mb-4 font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-center uppercase sm:text-left sm:text-4xl text-oak">How It
          Moves</h2>
        <hr class="w-4/5 mx-auto border-2 sm:w-full lg:w-4/5 border-oak sm:mx-0">
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-lg text-center sm:text-left">
        <p>
          The rook moves in straight lines, either horizontally or vertically, across the board. This allows it to
          control entire rows and columns, making it a formidable piece in open positions.
        </p>
        <p>
          This piece can move any number of squares in a straight line, but it cannot jump over other pieces. It is
          particularly powerful when placed on the same rank or file as another rook, forming a <span
            class="font-bold">rook battery</span>.
        </p>
        <p>
          The rook is also a key piece in endgames, where its ability to control open files and ranks can lead to
          decisive advantages.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-20">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="mb-4 font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-center uppercase sm:text-4xl text-oak">
        Key Facts
