      <hr class="w-2/5 mx-auto border-2 border-oak">
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-8 mx-auto max-w-96 md:max-w-none">
      {{> key-fact fact="Power on Open Files" description="Rooks thrive on open or half-open files, where their
      long-range movement allows them to control critical lines and pressure weak pawns effectively."}}

      {{> key-fact fact="Strength on Seventh Rank" description="A rook placed on the opponent's seventh rank can
      dominate, attacking vulnerable pawns and restricting the king's movement, often deciding games quickly."}}

      {{> key-fact fact="Behind Passed Pawns" description="In endgames, rooks are strongest behind passed pawns, either
      pushing their own forward or restraining the opponent's progress with constant pressure."}}

      {{> key-fact fact="Double Rooks' Pressure" description="Stacking two rooks on the same file or rank amplifies
      pressure, often overwhelming defensive resources and creating decisive tactical or positional threats."}}

      {{> key-fact fact="Back-Rank Mate" description="Rooks can deliver checkmate on the back rank if enemy pawns trap
      their king, making constant awareness of king safety essential."}}
    </div>
  </div>

